---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components";
import { Code as AstroCode } from "astro:components";
import Divider from "../../components/ui/Divider.astro";

//#region Code Snippets

const InputExample = `
// INPUT: data comes from the user
let response = prompt("Type yes or no").toLowerCase();
`;

const ListExample = `
// LIST: stores multiple related values
let answers = [];

answers.push("yes");
answers.push("no");
`;

const ProcedureExample = `
// STUDENT-DEVELOPED PROCEDURE with a PARAMETER
function analyzeAnswers(answerList)
{
  let score = 0;
  return score;
}
`;

const AlgorithmExample = `
// ALGORITHM inside the procedure
function analyzeAnswers(answerList)
{
  let score = 0;
  let i = 0;

  // ITERATION
  while (i < answerList.length)
  {
    // SELECTION
    if (answerList[i] === "yes")
    {
      score++;
    }

    i++;
  }

  return score;
}
`;

const OutputExample = `
// OUTPUT depends on processing
console.log("Yes count:", result);
`;

//#endregion
---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/ap-csp/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Create Performance Task Checklist</h1>
        <p class="text-muted">
          A practical, evidence-based checklist for AP CSP Create PT success.
        </p>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-4" />

        <!-- HOW TO USE -->
        <section>
          <h2>How to Use This Checklist</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Every checkbox should be an honest <b>yes</b>.</li>
            <li>If you can't point to it in your code, it doesn't count.</li>
            <li>Simple and explainable beats impressive and confusing.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- INPUT -->
        <section>
          <h3>1) Program &amp; Input</h3>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ My program responds to something the user does.</li>
            <li>☐ The user's input changes what the program does.</li>
            <li>☐ I can point to the exact line where input happens.</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-muted">
            If the user did nothing, the program would behave differently or not work.
          </p>

          <Code
            code={InputExample}
            frame="code"
            lang="javascript"
            title="Input Example"
            class="text-start"
          />
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- LIST -->
        <section>
          <h3>2) List (Array)</h3>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ I use one list that stores multiple related values.</li>
            <li>☐ The list is used more than once.</li>
            <li>☐ The program would be worse without this list.</li>
            <li>☐ I can explain why this list is better than separate variables.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code
            code={ListExample}
            frame="code"
            lang="javascript"
            title="List Example"
            class="text-start"
          />
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- PROCEDURE -->
        <section>
          <h3>3) Student-Developed Procedure (Function)</h3>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ I wrote this procedure myself.</li>
            <li>☐ It has at least one parameter.</li>
            <li>☐ It is called at least once.</li>
            <li>☐ It does meaningful work.</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-muted">
            The procedure does <b>not</b> need to be called more than once.
          </p>

          <Code
            code={ProcedureExample}
            frame="code"
            lang="javascript"
            title="Procedure Example"
            class="text-start"
          />
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- ALGORITHM -->
        <section>
          <h3>4) Algorithm (Inside the Procedure)</h3>

          <h4>Sequencing</h4>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ The procedure has multiple steps that run in order.</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-muted">
            If your procedure has more than one line that executes top-to-bottom,
            you have sequencing.
          </p>

          <h4>Selection</h4>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ The procedure uses an <AstroCode code="if" lang="javascript" inline theme="material-theme-ocean" /> statement.</li>
          </ul>

          <h4>Iteration</h4>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ The procedure uses a <b>while loop</b>.</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-muted">
            All three must appear inside the <b>same</b> student-developed procedure.
          </p>

          <Code
            code={AlgorithmExample}
            frame="code"
            lang="javascript"
            title="Algorithm Example (while + if)"
            class="text-start"
            showLineNumbers
          />
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- OUTPUT -->
        <section>
          <h3>5) Output</h3>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ The program produces visible output.</li>
            <li>☐ The output depends on user input and processing.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code
            code={OutputExample}
            frame="code"
            lang="javascript"
            title="Output Example"
            class="text-start"
          />
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- VIDEO -->
        <section>
          <h3>6) Video</h3>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ Shows user input.</li>
            <li>☐ Shows the program running.</li>
            <li>☐ Shows output.</li>
            <li>☐ No narration required.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- WRITTEN RESPONSES -->
        <section>
          <h3>7) Written Responses</h3>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ I reference my list, procedure, and algorithm.</li>
            <li>☐ I explain what the code does.</li>
            <li>☐ I answer exactly what the prompt asks.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <hr />

        <!-- FINAL CHECK -->
        <section>
          <h3>8) Final Sanity Check</h3>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>☐ I can explain my entire program calmly. If you can point to it and explain it calmly, AP will count it.</li>
            <li>☐ I did not add features "just in case."</li>
            <li>☐ Every major part of my code exists for a rubric reason.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
